name: paper production, newsprint, virgin | paper, newsprint | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/11830/documentation

This dataset represents the production of virgin newsprint paper in the region of Québec.;Virgin newsprint paper is mainly produces from wood chips but small amount of deinked pulp is too used in one site on the three under study. 

From reception of wood chips and other raw materials at the factory gate

This activity ends with virgin newsprint paper at factory gate.
The dataset includes wood handling, mechanical pulping, paper production, energy production on-site and internal waste water treatment.
The dataset does not include commercial and human activities.
category: C:Manufacturing/17:Manufacture of paper and paper products/170:Manufacture of paper and paper products/1701:Manufacture of pulp, paper and paperboard

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from one newsprint producer for three sites in the region of Québec used as average for the whole region.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: For unknown data, emissions for heat production from on-site fuels (light fuel oil, heavy fuel oil, natural gas and bark chips).have been extrapolated from ecoinvent v3.0 datasets of heat production. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Measured values for inputs and outputs based on data survey from one newsprint producer for three sites in the region of Québec.
